* About our love...

570
00:40:53,952 --> 00:40:57,756
- Hey.
- Hey.

571
00:40:57,789 --> 00:40:59,558
Dinah Washington.

572
00:40:59,591 --> 00:41:03,061
For the home,
Dinah Washington,
for the car.

573
00:41:03,094 --> 00:41:05,330
Dinah Washington
for your soul.

574
00:41:05,363 --> 00:41:08,099
Awww. I can't thank you
enough for this, Cory.

575
00:41:08,133 --> 00:41:09,835
No problem. That's fine.

576
00:41:09,868 --> 00:41:13,304
Listen, I'm about to close up.
You wanna play a game of pool?

577
00:41:13,338 --> 00:41:15,541
No, actually,
I'm kind of tired.

578
00:41:15,574 --> 00:41:18,143
I think I'm just gonna
go home and get some sleep,

579
00:41:18,176 --> 00:41:20,846
but I'll take a rain check.

580
00:41:20,879 --> 00:41:23,114
Okay,
I'll hold you to it.

581
00:41:23,148 --> 00:41:25,751
- Okay, thanks.
- Yeah.

582
00:41:28,554 --> 00:41:29,688
See you later.

583
00:41:39,765 --> 00:41:42,267
[telephone ringing]

584
00:41:49,040 --> 00:41:51,442
Now how does this thing work?

585
00:41:53,712 --> 00:41:55,113
Hello.

586
00:41:55,146 --> 00:41:58,149
Hello. Is Maggie there?

587
00:41:58,183 --> 00:42:00,919
No, she's not. 
 Who is this?

588
00:42:00,952 --> 00:42:04,956
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
I know who this is.

589
00:42:04,990 --> 00:42:08,927
Trickery will get you nowhere,
my pasta eating friend.

590
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:12,263
- What?  
- Whether I have a cat,
 whether I have a roommate,

591
00:42:12,297 --> 00:42:14,399
or whether I dance
in the nude till dawn,

592
00:42:14,432 --> 00:42:17,102
it's of no business of yours.

593
00:42:17,135 --> 00:42:19,170
Who is this?

594
00:42:19,204 --> 00:42:22,340
Oh, well,
I beg your pardon.

595
00:42:22,373 --> 00:42:25,310
You are speaking to the man
of the house,

596
00:42:25,343 --> 00:42:27,278
as if you didn't know.

597
00:42:27,312 --> 00:42:31,249
What man? I thought she lived
with a Rachel.

598
00:42:31,282 --> 00:42:34,986
I am Rachel and she does--

599
00:42:35,020 --> 00:42:37,989
or perhaps does not
live with me.

600
00:42:38,023 --> 00:42:40,325
Now you own up
to your identity.

601
00:42:40,358 --> 00:42:43,194
This is her father.

602
00:42:43,228 --> 00:42:47,265
Oh, can I take a message,
please?

603
00:42:47,298 --> 00:42:49,367
No message.

604
00:42:50,669 --> 00:42:52,537
Oh.

605
00:42:54,072 --> 00:42:58,276
* Somebody's in trouble *

606
00:43:11,056 --> 00:43:14,125
- Hello, Maggie.
- Hi, Tom.

607
00:43:17,696 --> 00:43:20,231
Thank you.

608
00:43:20,265 --> 00:43:22,868
That's a beautiful outfit.

609
00:43:22,901 --> 00:43:25,036
Thanks.

610
00:43:25,070 --> 00:43:29,841
So it took you a while
to call, but I'm awfully
glad you did.

611
00:43:29,875 --> 00:43:32,878
- Are you hungry?
- Actually, I am.

612
00:43:45,123 --> 00:43:47,325
Thank you.

613
00:43:49,828 --> 00:43:52,430
- [waiter] Enjoy your meal.
- [Tom] Thank you.

614
00:43:54,199 --> 00:43:56,367
Just a minute.

615
00:44:03,975 --> 00:44:06,712
Beautiful.

616
00:44:06,745 --> 00:44:08,680
What's this for?

617
00:44:08,714 --> 00:44:12,617
It had you written all
over it. You like it?

618
00:44:12,650 --> 00:44:15,086
I love it.

619
00:44:15,120 --> 00:44:17,655
Truth is I had
a dream about you

620
00:44:17,689 --> 00:44:19,858
and you were wearing
a hat just like that one.

621
00:44:19,891 --> 00:44:21,860
I had to see you
with it on.

622
00:44:21,893 --> 00:44:23,294
Are you disappointed?

623
00:44:23,328 --> 00:44:25,163
Not at all.

624
00:44:25,196 --> 00:44:27,933
Would you like to hear
about my dream?

625
00:44:27,966 --> 00:44:30,501
Not particularly.

626
00:44:30,535 --> 00:44:33,972
I would like to take you
somewhere tomorrow afternoon.

627
00:44:34,005 --> 00:44:35,941
Are you available?

628
00:44:35,974 --> 00:44:38,543
I suppose.

629
00:44:38,576 --> 00:44:40,912
Good.

630
00:44:42,313 --> 00:44:44,282
Where are we going?

631
00:44:44,315 --> 00:44:46,752
It's a surprise.

632
00:44:52,257 --> 00:44:54,860
- Mr. Roscoe.
- Hello, Douglas.

633
00:44:58,229 --> 00:45:00,365
- Douglas, I'd like you
 to meet Maggie.
- How do you do?

634
00:45:00,398 --> 00:45:03,068
- Maggie, this is
 my friend Douglas.
- How do you do?

635
00:45:03,101 --> 00:45:06,537
They've only been going
about 15 minutes.

636
00:45:06,571 --> 00:45:09,640
- How's Albert?
- Good.
 Yeah, he's doing great.

637
00:45:09,674 --> 00:45:11,442
Thanks for asking,
Douglas,

638
00:45:11,476 --> 00:45:13,278
and thanks for this.

639
00:45:13,311 --> 00:45:14,980
Anytime, Mr. Roscoe.

640
00:45:17,816 --> 00:45:19,350
I'm gonna be home the night
of the performance

641
00:45:19,384 --> 00:45:22,520
so the best
I could do is rehearsal.

642
00:45:29,327 --> 00:45:31,229
It's beautiful.

643
00:45:45,210 --> 00:45:47,445
[sneezes]

644
00:45:47,478 --> 00:45:49,580
- God bless you.
- That's all right.

645
00:45:49,614 --> 00:45:51,549
I'm only allergic
to a few things.

646
00:45:51,582 --> 00:45:53,218
What are you allergic to?

647
00:45:53,251 --> 00:45:56,855
Milk and perfume.
You must be wearing some.

648
00:45:56,888 --> 00:45:59,257
I am. I'll try
to remember that.

649
00:45:59,290 --> 00:46:01,259
I'd appreciate that.

650
00:46:01,292 --> 00:46:04,963
- So who's Albert?
- My son.

651
00:46:04,996 --> 00:46:08,733
- How long have you
 been divorced?
- Three years.

652
00:47:03,922 --> 00:47:06,224
Oh, my, you look nice.

653
00:47:06,257 --> 00:47:08,860
Thank you.
So do you, by the way.

654
00:47:08,894 --> 00:47:11,062
Thank you.

655
00:47:11,096 --> 00:47:12,964
Oh!

656
00:47:17,869 --> 00:47:19,104
Rent.

657
00:47:20,805 --> 00:47:24,275
You know, whenever a woman
tried to give me money,

658
00:47:24,309 --> 00:47:26,244
I'd always say,
"Put your money away,"

659
00:47:26,277 --> 00:47:29,247
or "I could never
take your money."

660
00:47:29,280 --> 00:47:31,917
But I always did.
[laughs]

661
00:47:31,950 --> 00:47:33,718
What a surprise.

662
00:47:33,751 --> 00:47:34,953
Okay, come on, get up.

663
00:47:34,986 --> 00:47:37,122
I'm gonna take you
on a picnic.

664
00:47:37,155 --> 00:47:39,124
- On a what?
- A picnic.

665
00:47:39,157 --> 00:47:41,426
- A picnic, come on.
- Oh, my God. Oh, no!

666
00:47:41,459 --> 00:47:43,261
It's good.
Come on, come on.

667
00:47:43,294 --> 00:47:45,230
Come on! Picnic, picnic.

668
00:47:45,263 --> 00:47:47,765
- All right, come on. [grunts]
- Whoopee! Whoopee!

669
00:47:47,798 --> 00:47:50,701
* We're going on a picnic,
we're going... *

670
00:47:50,735 --> 00:47:52,837
- * One bright day 
- * In the middle of the night

671
00:47:52,870 --> 00:47:55,140
- * In the middle of the night 
- * Two dead boys--

672
00:47:55,173 --> 00:47:58,043
Two dead boys? That doesn't
sound like much fun.

673
00:47:58,076 --> 00:47:59,410
- Come on!
- Come on, what?

674
00:47:59,444 --> 00:48:01,112
- It's a song.
- Go on.

675
00:48:01,146 --> 00:48:03,148
* One was blind
and the other couldn't see *

676
00:48:03,181 --> 00:48:06,117
No, no, that's
not happy enough.
Go back to the girl.

