00:48:10,956 --> 00:48:12,991
Oh, God!

679
00:48:13,024 --> 00:48:15,460
You forgot the butter.

680
00:48:15,493 --> 00:48:18,629
No, no, no,
it's still quite delicious.

681
00:48:18,663 --> 00:48:21,832
Hey, where's the credit
for even bringing food, huh?

682
00:48:25,203 --> 00:48:26,737
Where are your parents?

683
00:48:29,107 --> 00:48:31,609
That's a question out
of nowhere.

684
00:48:31,642 --> 00:48:33,979
Just on my mind.

685
00:48:36,781 --> 00:48:39,317
Well, my mother's dead,
and my father's in Portage.

686
00:48:39,350 --> 00:48:41,486
Why?

687
00:48:41,519 --> 00:48:44,755
Do you keep in touch
with your father?

688
00:48:44,789 --> 00:48:46,357
Not since I moved in.

689
00:48:46,391 --> 00:48:48,026
Why's that?

690
00:48:50,795 --> 00:48:52,998
My father and I never
got along too well,

691
00:48:53,031 --> 00:48:56,767
and, yes, I have tried
to work it out,

692
00:48:56,801 --> 00:49:00,638
but nothing ever changed
so it's part of the past now.

693
00:49:00,671 --> 00:49:02,473
And I'm over it.

694
00:49:04,342 --> 00:49:06,077
Uh-huh.

695
00:49:07,979 --> 00:49:10,081
Well...

696
00:49:10,115 --> 00:49:14,052
I'm gonna have
a little talk with him.

697
00:49:14,085 --> 00:49:15,586
You know?

698
00:49:15,620 --> 00:49:17,755
Find out what's going on.

699
00:49:21,092 --> 00:49:25,030
