about, man? I did you a favor.

761
00:54:06,010 --> 00:54:07,945
You call that a favor?

762
00:54:07,978 --> 00:54:09,280
Yeah, you're a singer.

763
00:54:09,314 --> 00:54:11,148
So what's the big deal
about singing a song?

764
00:54:11,181 --> 00:54:13,751
I give you an opportunity
thinking you can make
a gig out of it.

765
00:54:13,784 --> 00:54:15,653
So yeah,
I think that's a favor.

766
00:54:15,686 --> 00:54:18,055
Yeah, but I wasn't prepared.
The band wasn't prepared.

767
00:54:18,088 --> 00:54:19,990
You can't just throw me up
on stage like that.

768
00:54:20,024 --> 00:54:22,627
It was the wrong crowd.
I was terrified.

769
00:54:22,660 --> 00:54:25,296
I guess I'm just an idiot
for thinking a singer sings.

770
00:54:25,330 --> 00:54:26,931
I guess it takes more
than the right mood.

771
00:54:26,964 --> 00:54:28,666
You know what?
You're probably right, Maggie,

772
00:54:28,699 --> 00:54:30,868
'cause every time
I try to help out,
I screw it up.

773
00:54:30,901 --> 00:54:35,205
I wouldn't expect someone
like you with your little
perfect life to understand.

774
00:54:35,239 --> 00:54:37,942
Man, you have not
even lived through half

775
00:54:37,975 --> 00:54:41,412
of what I have lived through.

776
00:54:41,446 --> 00:54:43,748
I would have killed
to have somebody go out
of their way for me.

777
00:54:43,781 --> 00:54:46,116
You know what?
You probably just expect it.

778
00:54:46,150 --> 00:54:47,818
Yeah, all right,
I'm the asshole.

779
00:54:47,852 --> 00:54:50,921
I'm always the asshole.

780
00:55:38,068 --> 00:55:40,237
[woman] Maggie.

781
00:55:47,478 --> 00:55:49,346
Sweetheart.

782
00:55:54,752 --> 00:55:57,722
Mom.

783
00:55:57,755 --> 00:56:00,591
[sobbing]

784
00:56:00,625 --> 00:56:02,460
It's okay.

785
00:56:06,897 --> 00:56:09,233
Everything's gonna be okay.

786
00:56:17,475 --> 00:56:19,043
Is it?

787
00:56:24,749 --> 00:56:26,651
Mom?

788
00:56:35,025 --> 00:56:38,228
[music over dialogue]

789
00:57:06,323 --> 00:57:09,126
[music over dialogue]

790
00:57:18,803 --> 00:57:22,673
You know, I think some
of what Julia said is true.

791
00:57:22,707 --> 00:57:24,374
I should wanna sing
no matter what,

792
00:57:24,408 --> 00:57:28,979
and I shouldn't care
what anybody thinks
about me.

793
00:57:29,013 --> 00:57:30,481
You shouldn't be
able to shut me up

794
00:57:30,515 --> 00:57:35,285
and the thought
of what people think
just paralyzes me.

795
00:57:36,320 --> 00:57:37,855
I'm so embarrassed
that you had

796
00:57:37,888 --> 00:57:40,558
to see me walk off stage
like a scared little jackass.

797
00:57:40,591 --> 00:57:43,561
Don't--
Don't even think about that.

798
00:57:43,594 --> 00:57:46,897
Look, you have chosen
a difficult path,

799
00:57:46,931 --> 00:57:49,133
where extremely high hills

800
00:57:49,166 --> 00:57:52,136
and very deep valleys
just come with the territory.

801
00:57:52,169 --> 00:57:56,440
What happened last night
was part of the ride.

802
00:57:56,473 --> 00:57:59,009
True story.

803
00:57:59,043 --> 00:58:02,179
'81. Rolling Stones
are at the L.A. Coliseum.

804
00:58:02,212 --> 00:58:04,749
80,000 in attendance.
Prince opens for them.

805
00:58:04,782 --> 00:58:06,984
The crowd hates him.

806
00:58:07,017 --> 00:58:09,153
And not only is he
mercilessly booed,

807
00:58:09,186 --> 00:58:12,456
but they threw anything
and everything at him.

808
00:58:12,489 --> 00:58:16,594
I mean, 80,000 people
simultaneously wanted
that man off the stage.

809
00:58:16,627 --> 00:58:19,797
- So what did he do?
- He got the hell
 off the stage.

810
00:58:19,830 --> 00:58:23,000
Interestingly enough,
a reviewer wrote that
if he was capable

811
00:58:23,033 --> 00:58:26,270
of upsetting that many
people, he must have
been onto something.

812
00:58:26,303 --> 00:58:28,172
So now you didn't even
open your mouth

813
00:58:28,205 --> 00:58:30,040
and you got that kind
of reaction.

814
00:58:30,074 --> 00:58:32,910
So just think what's
in store for you.

815
00:58:32,943 --> 00:58:37,982
Something like this
wouldn't bring you
down, would it?

816
00:58:38,015 --> 00:58:41,418
I mean, I don't know.

817
00:58:41,451 --> 00:58:44,555
You know what I
really wanna find out--
I mean--

818
00:58:44,589 --> 00:58:46,791
look, I keep my life
as simple as possible.

819
00:58:46,824 --> 00:58:50,595
Owning a store is as much
responsibility as I care for.

820
00:58:50,628 --> 00:58:52,797
I think about getting rid
of it all the time.

821
00:58:52,830 --> 00:58:55,199
Give me
a Terry Southern novel

822
00:58:55,232 --> 00:58:57,902
and a Charles Brown LP
and I'm happy, you know?

823
00:58:57,935 --> 00:59:02,539
Life is too short
to do anything
but enjoy yourself.

824
00:59:02,573 --> 00:59:06,644
God, I wish I had your
peace and simplicity.

825
00:59:06,677 --> 00:59:10,948
You don't, but that's not
necessarily your choice.

826
00:59:10,981 --> 00:59:14,018
Yeah, well, it doesn't feel
like I have a choice.

827
00:59:14,051 --> 00:59:15,853
Right.

828
00:59:15,886 --> 00:59:18,756
Yeah, but if I
was more like Julia,

829
00:59:18,789 --> 00:59:21,892
it'd be so much easier.
She doesn't care what
people think about her.

830
00:59:21,926 --> 00:59:25,930
If somebody booed her,
she'd just flip 'em off
and keep doing her thing.

831
00:59:25,963 --> 00:59:28,332
So you have a few fears.

832
00:59:28,365 --> 00:59:30,434
So what? They're gonna
work themselves out.

833
00:59:30,467 --> 00:59:32,603
What matters,
what really matters

834
00:59:32,637 --> 00:59:35,405
is that you have it
in your heart.

835
00:59:35,439 --> 00:59:38,643
And no amount of money
can buy that.

836
00:59:38,676 --> 00:59:42,146
Look, and you gotta remember,
you could have run

837
00:59:42,179 --> 00:59:43,413
when they announced you,
but you didn't.

838
00:59:43,447 --> 00:59:45,115
You walked up out
onto that stage.

839
00:59:45,149 --> 00:59:47,251
And a lot of people,
believe me,

840
00:59:47,284 --> 00:59:49,186
a lot of people

841
00:59:49,219 --> 00:59:51,822
would never have even
gotten that far.

842
00:59:56,593 --> 00:59:59,664
You're the only one
I'd talk to about this.

843
01:00:01,331 --> 01:00:03,834
You're a good friend, Cory.

844
01:00:15,245 --> 01:00:18,382
My wish is...

845
01:00:18,415 --> 01:00:20,384
to live in the city

846
01:00:20,417 --> 01:00:23,520
because it's so different

847
01:00:23,553 --> 01:00:26,256
from what I grew up in.

848
01:00:28,292 --> 01:00:31,829
There's so many people there.
It's a place--

849
01:00:31,862 --> 01:00:33,330
I don't know.

850
01:00:33,363 --> 01:00:37,534
I'd have a freedom
that I've never known.

851
01:00:37,567 --> 01:00:40,270
Like I could take chances
with my life

852
01:00:40,304 --> 01:00:43,240
and it would be okay
to fail

853
01:00:43,273 --> 01:00:48,145
because there's so
many people there that,

854
01:00:48,178 --> 01:00:51,015
no one would care
or notice.

855
01:00:51,048 --> 01:00:54,184
No one but me.

856
01:00:56,020 --> 01:00:58,622
So why don't you go there?

857
01:00:58,655 --> 01:01:00,925
[laughs]

858
01:01:00,958 --> 01:01:05,662
One, money issues.

859
01:01:05,696 --> 01:01:07,798
And second...

860
01:01:11,235 --> 01:01:14,238
There's so many people,

861
01:01:14,271 --> 01:01:17,441
I'm afraid I'd just disappear

862
01:01:17,474 --> 01:01:21,278
and no one would care
or notice.

863
01:01:25,816 --> 01:01:29,119
Well, why don't we see
what we can do

864
01:01:29,153 --> 01:01:33,023
to get you there
and protect you

865
01:01:33,057 --> 01:01:35,225
so you don't disappear?

866
01:01:39,196 --> 01:01:43,267
- Tom hasn't called?
- Unh-unh.

867
01:01:43,300 --> 01:01:46,370
- Are you sure?
- Uh-huh.

868
01:01:46,403 --> 01:01:49,306
You didn't maybe forget
or something, did you?

869
01:01:49,339 --> 01:01:51,275
Unh-unh.

870
01:01:51,308 --> 01:01:55,679
- Phone never rang?
- Unh-unh.

871
01:01:55,712 --> 01:01:58,883
[sighs] Never rang, he says.

872
01:02:30,214 --> 01:02:32,682
[laughs]

873
01:02:32,716 --> 01:02:35,752
God, it's a good thing
I brought my cap along.

874
01:02:35,786 --> 01:02:37,587
The sun's right
on top of us.

875
01:02:37,621 --> 01:02:39,656
I know.
It's beautiful out.

876
01:02:39,689 --> 01:02:41,992
Nothing makes me happier
than a perfect summer's day.

877
01:02:42,026 --> 01:02:45,329
Striving to be that word
you just used is gonna
kill you.

878
01:02:45,362 --> 01:02:47,531
- You be careful.
- What do you mean?

879
01:02:47,564 --> 01:02:51,268
Oh, there's no use trying
to explain, my precious.

880
01:02:51,301 --> 01:02:53,137
You'll find out.

881
01:02:53,170 --> 01:02:56,106
Well, what if I don't?
Tell me.

882
01:02:56,140 --> 01:03:00,410
Well, let me ask you.
What is happy?

883
01:03:00,444 --> 01:03:04,681
Happy is when you
have a warm feeling
in your stomach,

884
01:03:04,714 --> 01:03:07,051
when it isn't tied
in knots.

885
01:03:07,084 --> 01:03:09,453
Happy's when you can get out
of bed in the morning.

886
01:03:09,486 --> 01:03:12,322
I see.
And you strive for that?

887
01:03:12,356 --> 01:03:14,691
- Sure.
- How?

888
01:03:14,724 --> 01:03:17,494
I don't know.
I guess I try
to change my life.

889
01:03:17,527 --> 01:03:22,099
I see. And in doing so,
do you accomplish happy?

890
01:03:22,132 --> 01:03:25,903
Not necessarily,
but at least I'm
doing something.

891
01:03:25,936 --> 01:03:29,706
- Doing something
 as in change?
- Yeah.

892
01:03:29,739 --> 01:03:31,641
Let me ask you
another question.

893
01:03:31,675 --> 01:03:36,346
Why are you courted by men,
but not in a relationship?

894
01:03:36,380 --> 01:03:38,482
- Why is that?
- [laughs]

895
01:03:38,515 --> 01:03:41,351
That's a loaded question
I don't care to answer.

896
01:03:41,385 --> 01:03:43,854
- I see.
- You see what?

897
01:03:43,888 --> 01:03:48,192
Do you not question
why you cherish such
unavailable men?

898
01:03:48,225 --> 01:03:50,227
Who's unavailable?

899
01:03:50,260 --> 01:03:54,331
Perhaps you should
tell me, hmm?

900
01:03:54,364 --> 01:03:56,400
I don't follow you.

901
01:03:56,433 --> 01:04:00,037
Let me ask you another
question on a completely
different subject.

902
01:04:00,070 --> 01:04:02,873
Do you like the Beatles?

903
01:04:02,907 --> 01:04:04,474
Yeah, I guess.

904
01:04:04,508 --> 01:04:07,544
Now what do you mean
by "I guess"?

905
01:04:07,577 --> 01:04:11,248
- Why wouldn't I?
- Precisely.

906
01:04:11,281 --> 01:04:13,150
What would happen
if you said,

907
01:04:13,183 --> 01:04:15,785
"I didn't like the Beatles,
never have and never will."
What would happen?

908
01:04:15,819 --> 01:04:17,487
I don't know.
I guess I wouldn't say that.

909
01:04:17,521 --> 01:04:20,324
But what if you genuinely
didn't like the Beatles?

910
01:04:20,357 --> 01:04:22,226
All right then, I'd say it.

911
01:04:22,259 --> 01:04:23,660
- You would?
- Yeah.

912
01:04:23,693 --> 01:04:25,795
But you'd feel a bit
apprehensive in saying so

913
01:04:25,829 --> 01:04:29,399
because you're supposed
to feel differently,
isn't that right?

914
01:04:29,433 --> 01:04:33,237
- You could say that.
- Yes, well,
 I hate the Beatles!

915
01:04:33,270 --> 01:04:36,240
I always have
and I always will!

916
01:04:36,273 --> 01:04:40,110
And I'll be damned if I won't
let the whole world know it.

917
01:04:40,144 --> 01:04:42,546
If one of their songs
comes on the radio,
I switch it off.

918
01:04:42,579 --> 01:04:46,683
And I'd do it in front
of a million people
if the opportunity arose.

919
01:04:46,716 --> 01:04:49,586
Try this one on for size.
I don't like Shakespeare.

920
01:04:49,619 --> 01:04:52,156
I hate Shakespeare!

921
01:04:52,189 --> 01:04:56,093
Shakespeare is
profoundly dull!

922
01:04:57,627 --> 01:05:00,164
What do you think?

923
01:05:00,197 --> 01:05:01,431
Wow.

924
01:05:01,465 --> 01:05:04,334
It's all very simple.

925
01:05:04,368 --> 01:05:08,138
Inner rebellion
followed by self triumph

926
01:05:08,172 --> 01:05:10,774
is a gift man was given.

927
01:05:10,807 --> 01:05:14,711
If he doesn't use that gift,
he becomes,

928
01:05:14,744 --> 01:05:18,515
as one may say, depressed.

929
01:05:18,548 --> 01:05:20,550
And I am correct
in saying this.

930
01:05:20,584 --> 01:05:24,888
A depressed man is
an utmost boring man.

931
01:05:24,921 --> 01:05:28,092
You're right about that.
But what do Shakespeare
and the Beatles have to do

932
01:05:28,125 --> 01:05:30,494
with happy
and my bad choice of men?

933
01:05:30,527 --> 01:05:34,298
Relationships are
a reflection of who you are.

934
01:05:34,331 --> 01:05:37,767
You, my dear,
are holding in a fight.

935
01:05:37,801 --> 01:05:40,670
Find out what you are
rebelling against
and express it.

936
01:05:40,704 --> 01:05:43,573
Scream it out loud
if you like. It's okay.

937
01:05:43,607 --> 01:05:47,744
Fight. Fight.
Happy has nothing
to do with change.

938
01:05:47,777 --> 01:05:50,747
Fight, fight,
fight, fight.

939
01:05:50,780 --> 01:05:53,417
Or that thing that won't
let you get out of bed

940
01:05:53,450 --> 01:05:55,652
in the morning
is gonna follow you.

941
01:06:01,525 --> 01:06:05,529
Time you found out who
or what is following you.

942
01:06:53,377 --> 01:06:55,145
Tom.

943
01:07:03,787 --> 01:07:05,855
Hello, I'm Mrs. Roscoe.

944
01:07:29,613 --> 01:07:32,216
[alarm ringing]

945
01:07:38,222 --> 01:07:39,923
[turns off alarm]

946
01:07:53,737 --> 01:07:57,907
Fireflies. Whoo!

947
01:07:57,941 --> 01:08:01,145
I wanna talk about my obvious
bad choice of men.

948
01:08:02,579 --> 01:08:04,414
I'm sorry.
What did you say?

949
01:08:04,448 --> 01:08:07,717
That day in the park
you said some things to
me that I wanna talk about.

950
01:08:07,751 --> 01:08:10,820
You said something about
my choice of men being related

951
01:08:10,854 --> 01:08:13,990
to my happiness
or my unhappiness.

952
01:08:14,023 --> 01:08:18,495
Yes, that. May I have
a cup of tea first?

953
01:08:18,528 --> 01:08:19,896
No, damn it,
explain yourself.

954
01:08:19,929 --> 01:08:22,299
- All right!
- All right.

955
01:08:22,332 --> 01:08:24,968
What is the question?

956
01:08:26,736 --> 01:08:30,140
All right, I admit
I've crashed again.

957
01:08:32,409 --> 01:08:35,679
Tom's married.

958
01:08:35,712 --> 01:08:37,947
I figured as much.

959
01:08:37,981 --> 01:08:40,317
Why didn't you say something?

960
01:08:40,350 --> 01:08:42,719
Oh, now, Maggie, really?

961
01:08:42,752 --> 01:08:45,021
You would never
have believed me.

962
01:08:45,054 --> 01:08:47,291
Besides, it was
only a hunch.

963
01:08:47,324 --> 01:08:49,459
Tell me why you would
have a hunch.

964
01:08:49,493 --> 01:08:52,196
Tell me why you say
that I choose bad men.

965
01:08:52,229 --> 01:08:55,565
I believe I said
unavailable men, not bad.

966
01:08:55,599 --> 01:09:00,570
I also asked you a question
in that park that day.
Do you remember?

967
01:09:00,604 --> 01:09:02,772
- No. What?
- Think.

968
01:09:02,806 --> 01:09:05,575
- I don't know. What?
- I asked you what

969
01:09:05,609 --> 01:09:07,043
or who you were
running away from,

970
01:09:07,076 --> 01:09:09,679
which of course inevitably
came along with you

971
01:09:09,713 --> 01:09:11,681
when you were trying
to change your life.

972
01:09:11,715 --> 01:09:14,284
I don't know. Nothing.

973
01:09:14,318 --> 01:09:16,052
Oh. Nothing.

974
01:09:16,085 --> 01:09:18,488
All right. All right.
Nothing.

975
01:09:18,522 --> 01:09:21,024
Fine. You know what?
I don't need you.
I don't need anybody!

976
01:09:21,057 --> 01:09:23,493
- You just hold it there,
 young lady.
- What?

977
01:09:23,527 --> 01:09:26,730
You're wrong,
and it's about time
you realized it.

978
01:09:26,763 --> 01:09:29,866
Okay, you have five seconds
to explain yourself or
I am gonna lose it.

979
01:09:29,899 --> 01:09:31,801
- You do need people.
- I do not.

980
01:09:31,835 --> 01:09:34,504
You do too.
You even need your father.

981
01:09:34,538 --> 01:09:38,007
Oh, my father.
My father doesn't even love me.
How can I possibly need the man?

982
01:09:38,041 --> 01:09:41,378
You've done a fine job
of convincing yourself
of that, haven't you?

983
01:09:41,411 --> 01:09:43,913
But you better convince
yourself otherwise and soon.

984
01:09:43,947 --> 01:09:48,452
Every moment you shut yourself
off from people because you
think you don't need them,

985
01:09:48,485 --> 01:09:50,687
you're denying yourself life.

986
01:09:50,720 --> 01:09:52,856
How could you
say that to me?

987
01:09:52,889 --> 01:09:55,124
How could you of all people
say that to me, Rachel?

988
01:09:55,158 --> 01:09:58,161
You are the definition
of loner.

989
01:09:58,194 --> 01:10:02,098
How many people do you need?
Hmm?

990
01:10:02,131 --> 01:10:03,867
[sighs]

991
01:10:05,402 --> 01:10:07,337
None.

992
01:10:08,538 --> 01:10:10,940
Because there's no one left.

993
01:10:13,443 --> 01:10:15,712
I made your mistake.

994
01:10:15,745 --> 01:10:18,848
Yeah, but you made it
for a reason.

995
01:10:18,882 --> 01:10:20,650
So what was it?

996
01:10:20,684 --> 01:10:23,753
We all have secrets.

997
01:10:25,489 --> 01:10:27,957
It's only now that I can see

998
01:10:27,991 --> 01:10:32,128
that I repelled
so many relationships

999
01:10:32,161 --> 01:10:35,499
in my life that I should
have cherished.

1000
01:10:36,766 --> 01:10:38,167
Yeah, well,

1001
01:10:38,201 --> 01:10:41,405
I'm not rejecting any
relationships worth having.

1002
01:10:41,438 --> 01:10:44,774
- So I guess I'm doing okay.
